The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, May 17, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, May 16: A promoter, Gulam Rabbani, was shot at by goons who failed to drag him into a car on Linton Street this evening as he raised an alarm . 

 The first bullet missed the 32-year-old. The second grazed his knee. He was taken to a local clinic and released after first-aid. 

 Durgapur: Sudipto Goon, a CPI councillor of the municipal corporation here, was arrested on Monday after his wife Keya, 31, died in a blaze. She allegedly set herself afire at their Durgapur Thermal Power Station Colony home, 200 km from Calcutta. Her father Kanailal Majumdar said Goon tortured her and demanded money from him often. 

 Calcutta: The results of this years madarsa exams will be declared on Friday. They will be available at the Calcutta Information Centre and on the Net. The madarsa board president said the marks can be seen on www.banglarmukh.com and www.wbgov.com 

 Calcutta: Seven Great Eastern Hotel employees collected ERS forms on Monday and one of them submitted it. Out of over 400 hotel employees, 19 have collected the forms, the deadline for submitting which expires on Wednesday. 

 Calcutta: Governor Gopal Gandhi on Monday expressed shock at the plastic pollution in the Darjeeling hills. At a meeting with tourism director M.K. Sengupta and secretary T.K. Barman, he said he saw plastic bags littering the region during a trip and that could ruin tourism.




